After a disruption of services in eThekwini today (17 November) refuse collection and street sweeping services which were affected by the Durban Solid Waste illegal strike action have resumed. eThekwini Municipality has requested residents to take out their refuse bags on their normal collection days. “We would like to thank all residents for their patience during this time,” said the municipality. Ethekwini spokesperson Msawakhe Mayisela, said the leadership of the municipality met with the unions representing the workers to ascertain what their grievances were and prioritised the matter. The city apologised to residents and regrets any inconvenience caused.